OL,3,CTax payers paid 'steep price' for Home
OL,4,COffice asylum housing mistakes ` report
OL,6,FThe Home Office's purchase of a
OL,7,Fderelict prison for #15.4 million
OL,8,Fbefore deciding it cannot be used to
OL,9,Fhouse asylum seekers has raised
OL,10,Fconcerns over its ability to stop such
OL,11,Fan "unacceptable waste" of public
OL,12,Fmoney from happening again, a new
OL,13,Freport has warned.
OL,15,FThe Public Accounts Committee found
OL,16,Fthe Home Office "rushed" to spend
OL,17,Fpublic money to cut costs for
OL,18,Fsupporting asylum seekers, but has
OL,19,F"very little to show for its efforts".
