OL,3,CTax payers paid 'steep price' for Home
OL,4,COffice asylum housing mistakes ` report
OL,6,FThe publication from MPs released on
OL,7,FWednesday read: "The Home Office
OL,8,Frepeatedly emphasised that it was
OL,9,Fworking at pace to reduce its reliance
OL,10,Fon costly hotel accommodation for
OL,11,Fasylum seekers, but this does not
OL,12,Fexcuse it from its responsibility to
OL,13,Fsafeguard taxpayers' money.
OL,15,F"As we have previously found, in some
OL,16,Fcases these programmes have cost more
OL,17,Fthan the alternative of using hotels."
OL,26,@oD@QOUwD@AOUyD@fO]
