OL,3,CTax payers paid 'steep price' for Home
OL,4,COffice asylum housing mistakes ` report
OL,6,FCommittee chairman, Sir Geoffrey
OL,7,FClifton-Brown, said: "Northeye was one
OL,8,Fof a series of failed Home Office
OL,9,Facquisitions for large asylum
OL,10,Faccommodation sites, totalling a cost
OL,11,Fto the public purse of almost #100
OL,12,Fmillion of taxpayers' money.
OL,14,F"Treasury rules for safeguarding
OL,15,Fpublic money are there for a reason
OL,16,Fand should only be overridden in
OL,17,Fextreme circumstances. This case
OL,18,Fclearly demonstrates why those
OL,19,Fsafeguards should normally be
OL,20,Ffollowed."
OL,26,@oD@VOUvD@AOU|D@JO]
